        <h3>KUMAONI WEDDING:</h3>
        <p>
            Kumaoni weddings focus on age-old rituals like Naandi (invoking ancestors) and Mehendi ceremonies. The bride and groom wear traditional attire, with the bride adorned in a yellow sari and gold jewelry, including the iconic nath. The event is marked by folk music and jhora dance, highlighting Kumaon’s rich heritage.
        </p>
        <img src="" alt="">
        <h3>JAUNSARI WEDDING:</h3>
        <p>
            Jaunsari weddings, celebrated by the Jaunsari tribe, often follow polygamy or polyandry traditions in some areas. The rituals include unique customs like chanduli, where the bride is welcomed to her new home with symbolic gestures. The wedding is accompanied by vibrant folk dances and music, reflecting the tribal identity.
        </p>
        <img src="" alt="">
        <h3>RAJPUT WEDDING:</h3>
        <p>
            Rajput weddings in Uttarakhand are grand and elaborate, emphasizing honor and tradition. Rituals like Tilak, Haldi, and Baraat are conducted with pomp, and the groom wears a sword as a symbol of valor. The ceremonies are steeped in Rajput pride and often include cultural performances.
        </p>
        <img src="" alt="">
        <h3>BHOTIYA WEDDING</h3>
        <p>
            Bhotiya weddings, celebrated by the Bhotiya tribe, feature rituals deeply influenced by Tibetan culture and Buddhism. They are known for their spiritual elements, including prayers to deities and the use of traditional chants. The bride wears a woolen attire called chon and silver jewelry, reflecting the high-altitude lifestyle.
        </p>
